name: non-specific protein-tyrosine kinase
comment: Unlike EC 2.7.10.1, receptor protein-tyrosine kinase, this protein-tyrosine kinase does not have a transmembrane domain. In the human genome, 32 non-specific protein-tyrosine kinases have been identified and these can be divided into ten families [1].

references.title: The protein tyrosine kinase family of the human genome.
